21/11/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliament approved on Tuesday (November 20th) the nomination of Enkeled Alibeaj to assume the post of justice minister, which was vacated by Ilir Rusmajli a week ago amid corruption allegations.
In other news Tuesday, opposition Socialist Party (SP) leader Edi Rama predicted early elections will be held next year. During a meeting with farmers, Rama accused the government of ignoring their problems. He urged them to protest chronic power and water shortages, promising such issues would be addressed when the SP returns to power. (Korrieri, Koha Jone, Shekulli - 21/11/07; Balkanweb, Top-Channel - 20/11/07)
